You are redesigning Thamos6 (T6), a premium SOC utility web app.

GOAL
Stop the “tri-pane drift”. The product is a smart IOC scanner like VirusTotal’s UX:
- One universal input (paste anything: IP, URL, domain, hash, extension ID)
- Auto-detect type and route automatically to the correct results page
- Clean, structured results pages with only the most useful fields surfaced first
- Raw JSON always available but collapsed by default

NAV / IA
- Top nav should have only two primary modes:
  1) Scanner (default)  — the universal input + results pages
  2) Intel Stream       — the curated RSS / threat intel feed (work later)
- Keep a subtle “Tools/Extras” overflow if needed, but Scanner is the hero.

SCANNER HOME (like VirusTotal home)
- A large universal input bar (centered, premium)
- Short “What we check” section with icons + sources:
  - VirusTotal (hash/url/domain)
  - urlscan.io (url screenshots + redirects)
  - AbuseIPDB (IP abuse confidence + categories + recent reports)
  - ipinfo (ASN/org/location)
  - ProxyCheck (TOR/VPN/proxy detection + provider name)
- No “Smart IOC Intake” headline needed; branding is “Thamos6”.

ROUTING / FLOW
- When user submits, auto-detect type and navigate:
  - /ip/:value
  - /url/:value
  - /domain/:value
  - /hash/:value
  - /extension/:id
- Show a slim progress line showing which sources were queried (only for the sources we have keys for).
- Raw sources section: collapsed by default.

RESULTS PAGE DESIGN (structured cards, no clutter)
For each type, build a clean page with:
1) Verdict header:
   - risk badge + score + “why” bullets (3–6 bullets max)
2) Key facts row:
   - IP: ASN, org, country, hosting/DC yes/no, TOR/VPN/proxy yes/no, provider name
   - URL: final URL, redirects count, screenshot/thumb, domain, VT detections, urlscan verdict
   - Hash: VT detections ratio, popular threat label, file type, size, first seen/last seen
   - Domain: registrar/created/age, hosting, VT domain reputation if available
3) Evidence cards:
   - AbuseIPDB: confidence %, total reports, top categories, most recent report summary
   - ProxyCheck: TOR/VPN/proxy flags + provider + risk-type notes
   - urlscan: screenshot, requests summary, chains (redirects), if available
   - VirusTotal: detection ratio + tags + community score, top engines (collapsed list)

CONTRADICTION / VARIANCE SURFACING
If different sources disagree (e.g., ipinfo says one country but another source says unknown), show a “Source variance” mini-card:
- Field name + values by source (small table)
- Confidence hint (“Prefer ipinfo for ASN/org; prefer ProxyCheck for VPN provider name; prefer AbuseIPDB for abuse categories”)

ACTIONS
Top-right actions on results pages:
- Copy clean summary
- Copy IOCs JSON
- Add to Watchlist
- Add Case Note

STYLE
- Crisp enterprise dark theme (like current app), readable typography, consistent spacing
- Cards with clear section headers; raw JSON is always accessible but not noisy
- Keep performance in mind: only call sources with existing keys

IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
- This is a React + TS + Tailwind app.
- Keep components modular (ResultHeader, KeyFacts, SourceStatus, EvidenceCard, VarianceCard, RawJsonCollapse, ActionsBar).
- Do not reintroduce a tri-pane.